    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pieces of timber inserted in a roof, floor, or wooden partition to support a header, which in turn supports the ends of the joists, rafters, or studs. Also, small horizontal beams, as in a floor, into which the ends of one or more joists are framed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010761/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stukken hout die in een dak, vloer of houten scheidingswand worden gezet ter ondersteuning van een bovendorpel, die op zijn beurt de uiteinden van dwarsbalken, daksparren of standvinken ondersteunt. Ook voor kleine horizontale balken, zoals bij een vloer,  die de uiteinden van een of meer steunbalken omgeven.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052414/Dictionary of building construction (1959)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>置入屋頂、樓層或木造隔間，以支撐丁磚的木片，進而支撐托樑、椽條或壁柱之端點。亦指例如在樓板中，可框固一至多條托樑端點的小型水平橫樑。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
